Pure beauty and inspiration at the incredible pre-Colombian museo of #Diego Rivera @anahuacalli in conversation with the pieces of @almaallen 
Thank you for the invitation it was truly an honor 🙏🏽✨

petits poèmes fleurissent dans l'atelier 🪷// 
I get used to seeing things I have made often. Sometimes even bored and switch things around. Then I move them again and disorganize and re organize but the best compositions sometimes happen when I’m not thinking, when I’m just cleaning and I find little poems bloom around the studio.

Our sculptural translucent porcelain luminaries are truly magical… this one in @tgopnik home. 🕯️🪷✨

These pieces are are sculpted and pinched to the finest thickness of the porcelain so that light can shine through. Sometimes there are cracks, but that is also part of their delicacy. Inspired by corals, marine shapes and flowers, each one becomes one more creature in our beautiful garden. 
DM x purchase

When we see ourselves as one with nature // when we recognize the beauty of ourselves as one would with a flower // when you recognize your potential to be an expression of your internal beauty… then, we bloom. 🪷

Can’t wait to show you the new work
Save the date, April 12, 2023 with @blackbrickproject

Van Gogh vibes at the studio today with one of my favorites, El Roce vase which means “the brushing against” or lightly touching. These vases come alive through flower arrangements… Feliz Primavera 🧞💐

Part of Los Korales series, a set of functional sculptures inspired by the natural shapes of rhizomes and mammalian cardiovascular organs that morph into floral installations; hand sculpted ceramic stoneware that features two gently intertwined necks emanating from a shared body.

Somos de la tierra// we are from the earth 
Reflexions of life cycles and continuity 🐛🦋

Learning to be a vessel 🏺
To carry my own weight, 
to contain love, 
to contain fear, 
sadness, anger
and the collection of time.
What do we look like if we were to take these forms?
In what unit are lightness & mirth measured?
How much of these can a body carry? 
Are we not just carcasses of experiences mixed with a little stardust? 
I love the theory of our soul weighing 21 grams… although in certain moments it feels so much heavier or significantly lighter. 

It is said that vases represent the shape of the womb.
Exploring, questioning and embarking into a journey that can only be walked through, birthing questions & emotions that connect me to the collective unconscious… 🔥
How beautiful to have a self portrait of us as vases, containing all our majesty and imperfections as one glorious masterpiece. 

Rolleiflex 🎞️ @matteoprodani

An Ode to Spring // 
Longing for the eternal sunshine of the summer.
Creeping, unfolding and unfurling it’s leaves.
The verticality of water,
whispering drops at endless times of the day.
Tiny Mirrors elegantly arranged 
 on the tops of leaves,
perfect water fountains 
for big and small.

💐 @hellabloom 
📷 @austinnelsonphoto

My forever favorite in bloom 🪷
//
Braids are a strong archetype in my memory.
Thick black sculptures swaying like long tree roots, reaching for the earth.
I remember my mother.
combing my hair at night as she put me to bed, weaving fairytales of love and adventure.
The stoic brown Venuses that graced the streets with their colorful clothes and black ropes.
Feminine, strong and graceful.

I was once told that women should never cut their hair as they are the roots of our mind- tree... such a beautiful image. 🧠🌳

In the pandemic. With a little too much Imagination and perhaps too much time braids bloom flowers.
Self portrait with braid, 2020

“But I love your feet only because they walked upon the earth and upon the wind and upon the waters, until they found me.”
- Pablo Neruda.

As the years go by, I keep coming to this place that is for the hopelessly romantic. And no, I don’t mean that to go you need to be with a significant other, I refer to the air, and charm of it all. 
To be swiped away just by breathing.
A perfectly frothy cappuccino @cibreo_firenze with velvet chairs and wood ceilings covered in roses. How hard is it not to be enchanted with the delicious candy colored marble slabs of the @duomodifirenze , the heavenly creatures and saints hand sculpted by Donatello or Michelangelo  @museodelbargello that they almost want you to relive the story of pygmalion? The dew colored eyes of Botticelli’s Venus, the perfection of David, the golden hue of Ponte Vecchio as I eat away my gelato…
Oh Florence, you truly are a gift to all my senses.

The millisecond, 
when a horses’ hooves 
float 
off the ground. 
The suspension 
of & in time. 
A floating, fleeting
 moment. 
The vastness of
the universe,
in nothing. 
What we cannot see 
but we definitely feel. 
Life, 
hidden in between 
all those secrets, 
depths, and greyscales. 
How lucky am I 
to be hidden 
in one of those petals 
of history. 
In that metamorphoses, 
that never ending 
developing of 
imperfection and transcendence.
Even more lucky, 
To share it 
with you.

……..
📷 @austinnelsonphoto

resembling wings. 
I close my eyes and

An eternal embrace.
I am here

When your tears reach the ground and nurture your own growth, wings bloom inside the deepest, darkest corners of your mind. 
The mycelium of life connects, feeds and expands into a greater knowledge and sense of self. 
Hopefully those channels, of our deepest self, can expand into a greater consciousness of our would and toward each other

El Chamán, watercolor on cotton, 2023

This painting makes me remember the wonderful words of @jerrysaltz describing the importance of artists in societies: 

“All art is a kind of exorcism and communion. Artists are like shamans living at the edges of our village, making things that might be useful to us.”

Such a pleasure to discover an article about my work from art/ fashion magazine @issue_cl from Chile! Thank you for the lovely words Camila, it was beautiful to share a little bit about me and my work with you and your team🙏🏽✨

An Ode to a Hand.
What “healing” looks like.
It is only when we permit ourselves to heal, 
when we make space and time 
To not be able to do, 
To move, to be you.

A feeling of apnea.
That combustion of carbon dioxide inside, 
like a venom that turns into medicine. 
That is perfect moment to explore, to go in, to let go.
Here is where we must
learn to forgive ourselves;
To let the body heal 
To feel 
And also the not feeling, 
not doing that is so frustrating.

To have the patience of a leaf cutter ant

Nonetheless, I am grateful for the much beauty I have encountered along the way… this journey doesn’t stop, we keep going, as our body parts don’t define who we are. 
That, is defined by what we do. 
🚀🎆

And when my roots 
are dehydrated, 
they expand, 
stretch and extend. 
We search for meaning in between letters,
In the rustle of the leaves, 
Or the warmth of a friendly smile. 
Searching for connection 
When the world is upside down, 
We must give water to our roots 
Fertilize our hearts
So we may stand 
Strong 
And always, together.
Gracias bosque, arcoíris y sol y  @matteoprodani  @kunval @mirko.musmeci @jessedsmiley for being such lightness and joy in my life

GRACIAS de todo corazón for all your beautiful life wishes, kind words, texts, calls, wonderful acapella singing, affectionate gestures and demonstrations of love. I am humbled by your outpour of attention and am immensely grateful to have you supporting me and encouraging me. Thank you for believing in me, For supporting my work, for your donations that to helped me make a very generous gift to two beautiful charities a couple weeks ago… @ifawglobal & @globalgiving 
I feel really grateful to have a banquet of abundance in such trying times. 

It’s been hard to focus on the goodness of life with so much horror happening around us. That reptilian brain, of seeing what i/ we lack and not how much we/ I actually have. 
These past couple of weeks have been heart breaking and I feel deeply for those that are suffering, persecuted and without food. For those that don’t have the luxury of sleeping, those whose wounds have been opened and can’t feel safe. I send my heart to you.

As many of you know, this year my hand injury has been the greatest teacher of patience, self love and complete abandonment. Learning that an experience is only a failure when we don’t grow. That sometimes it’s ok to just wake up and breathe. That a body part doesn’t define who we are, that we’re never alone when we have ourselves (& Toulouse). ♥️
This year has gifted me many lessons and I thank the universe for each one. 
I pray that this world grows a bigger heart and that the goodness of humanity beams stronger in the darkness, I see you all 🙏🏽✨

Gracias vida, porque aunque no tengo los ojos para ver todas y cada una de tus bendiciones, espero tener el corazón abierto para poder sentirlas todas.

For those that know me and what a rollercoaster my life has been this year, you know this project is super close to my heart.
This studio, is not only the place where I create but its a place I want to share with you. A tiny corner in this concrete jungle of warmth, where the soul can expand and create. A safe space to express, celebrate & get together… it’s finally coming along and I can’t wait to share it with you! 

While some small details are still missing, the studio is up and running and is available for bookings to be rented out for your private events & holiday parties. In this space we can curate company events, private workshops, group or private art classes and more! 

Feel free to DM me with any questions or email me at the link in bio. 
Thank you all who have accompanied me on this journey, my soul is eternally grateful. 
Todo mi amor, F

Prendo velas en su honor. 🕯️🌼
Les tejo un tapete de pétalos de cempasúchil  para que regresen un ratito más conmigo. 
Te pongo tu cubita, tu vinito, tu agüita. 
Pongo a Chavela y me echo un mezcalito a su salud. 
Que orgullo haber caminado entre sus pasos y hallan podido ser maestros en mi vida. 
Para los nuestros, para los que ya no nos acompañan, que sea ligero el camino a casa. 
Para los que están, tomemos nuestro corazón palpaitante y celebremos la vida.
// 
I light candles in your honor.
I weave tapestries with petals of marigolds so you can find your way to me. 
I pour you a cuba libre, your wine, your water. 
I play Chavela Vargas and drink a mezcalito with you.
What an honor to have walked next to you and have you be my teachers in this life.
For those that aren’t with us, may their journey be lighter home.
For those that are, May we take our beating hearts and celebrate life together. 

📸 @raulpina.fotografo 
💄 @sanchezsalon

Pasithea, Greek goddess of rest, relaxation, meditation, hallucination and all other states of altered consciousness is also wife of Hypnos, god of sleep and one of the three charities. 
Her name translated- the prefix pasis can mean “all”, “possessed” or “acquired” and the suffix thea (which is also the name of a Titan of prophecy), means “sight”, “seeing”, “contemplation”, “goddess” or “divine” Generally it is seen as meaning “all-seeing” - a hint to her ties with hallucinogens. *SOLD

I made this painting yesterday with with a lot of emotions in my heart. 
It seems difficult to ignore the dreadful events happening in the world, to hide in the consumerism of the holidays without taking the time to give ourselves space. A space to mourn, to cry, to feel what hurts. To know that pain is a reminder of our humanity and an opportunity for growth.

This felt like a different Christmas and wishing for it to be “merry”, feels naif.
Though I wasn’t next to my beloved family I am blessed to know I have their love. I am fortunate to have beautiful friendships and those dear to me, are like little pieces of my heart dancing around in the world. I am healthy, though parts of me are not super well, I am in the process of healing. I have a tiny but beautiful home I can come every night and a hound that loves me like I’m the best human on this earth… And, I have you. 

Gracias Vida.

May these days next to our treasures remind us of how blessed we are. May our hearts beat stronger to love, forgive and stand up for what is right.
For the people who aren’t close to their loved ones, those who are lost, hungry and alone, for those who are suffering the horrors of war, my heart is close to yours. May we find a way to grow through our differences and turn our surroundings into an enchanting biodiverse jungle with all sorts of creatures and exotic fruits.

Con amor, F

Jacques Brel // “I wish you endless dreams and the furious desire to realize some of them. I wish you to love what must be loved, and to forget what must be forgotten. I wish you passions. I wish you silences. I wish you birdsongs as you wake up and children’s laughter. I wish you to respect the differences of others, because the worth and virtues of each person often remain to be discovered. I wish you to resist the stagnation, the indifference, and the negative values of our time. I wish you at last to never to give up the search, for adventure, life, love. For life is a wonderful adventure and no reasonable person should give it up without a tough fight. I wish you above all to be yourself, proud of being and happy, for happiness is our true destiny.”
